title: Power Sports Weekend Oct 17-18: 2015 Washington Snowmobile & Power Sports Expo and Swap Meet
text:
SOURCE Washington State Snowmobile Association
Thousands of power sports enthusiasts are expected at the 2015 Washington Snowmobile & Power Sports Expo and Swap Meet - Oct. 17 to 18 - at the Washington State Fair Event Center in Puyallup.
PUYALLUP, Wash. For the first time in the Northwest, a power sports weekend - the chance for sports-minded people to experience the latest in motorsports - at a mega all power sports show.
The giant expo -- the 2015 Washington Snowmobile & Power Sports Expo and Swap Meet on Saturday and Sunday, Oct. 17 to 18, at the Washington State Fair Event Center in Puyallup .
The show includes the latest models in power sports and other fun, informative highlights:
Snowmobiles Snow bikes Motorcycles ATVs UTVs Personal watercrafts - jet skis Swap meet Free safety seminars on Saturday noon to 5 p.m. https://vimeo.com/142448936
Yes, the focus will be on safety: " Better Rides, Better Riders! "
Seminars will include the Safe Rider Snowmobile Seminar for 12-to-16-year-olds to earn their Snowmobile Safety Certificate . To register, call Washington State Parks at 1 (360) 902-8684 or email: winter@parks.wa.gov .
Admission is $10 and children 12 and under get free admission.
Expo hours: Saturday, 9 a.m. to 6 p.m. - Sunday, 9 a.m. to 2 p.m.
This event is hosted by the Washington State Snowmobile Association. For more information visit www.wssa.us .
